Build the MeetDorkBotStep onboarding component with two phases: name/setup and personality slider tuning.

**File: apps/client/src/layers/features/onboarding/ui/MeetDorkBotStep.tsx (new)**

The component has two internal phases:

**Phase 1 — Name & Setup:**
- Agent name input pre-filled with 'dorkbot' (editable, kebab-case validated using validateAgentName)
- Directory path shown as muted secondary text: `~/.dork/agents/{name}/` (updates as name changes)
- Template picker: collapsed accordion 'Choose a starter template'. Default: Blank (no template). Most users skip this.
- 'Next: Personality' button advances to Phase 2

**Phase 2 — Personality (the experience):**

Five trait sliders using @radix-ui/react-slider, each with 5 discrete stops:

| Trait      | Level 1      | Level 3  | Level 5   |
| ---------- | ------------ | -------- | --------- |
| Tone       | Serious      | Balanced | Playful   |
| Autonomy   | Ask first    | Balanced | Act alone |
| Caution    | Conservative | Balanced | Bold      |
| Detail     | Terse        | Balanced | Thorough  |
| Creativity | By the book  | Balanced | Inventive |

All default to level 3 (Balanced).

Each slider renders:
```tsx
<div className="space-y-2">
  <div className="flex justify-between text-sm">
    <span className="text-muted-foreground">{leftLabel}</span>
    <span className="font-medium">{traitName}</span>
    <span className="text-muted-foreground">{rightLabel}</span>
  </div>
  <Slider
    min={1}
    max={5}
    step={1}
    value={[traits[traitKey]]}
    onValueChange={([val]) => setTraits(prev => ({ ...prev, [traitKey]: val }))}
    onPointerDown={() => setIsReacting(true)}
    onPointerUp={() => setTimeout(() => setIsReacting(false), 600)}
  />
</div>
```

**Live personality preview** — speech-bubble element above sliders:
```tsx
const previewText = useDeferredValue(getPreviewText(traits));
const previewKey = useMemo(() => hashPreviewText(previewText), [previewText]);

<div className="rounded-lg border bg-muted/50 p-4">
  <AnimatePresence mode="wait">
    <motion.p
      key={previewKey}
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 4 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -4 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.2 }}
      className="text-sm text-muted-foreground"
    >
      {previewText}
    </motion.p>
  </AnimatePresence>
</div>
```

useDeferredValue debounces rapid slider scrubbing so the crossfade doesn't fire on every pixel of drag.

